      <bioghist id="aspace_10ccd10af703370383cdfd05d22b019b">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>The Rev. Daniel O. Morton (1788 December 21-1852 March 25) was ordained 1814 June 30 and
            served as Congregational pastor and evangelist in Rochester, VT (1814-1831),
            Springfield, VT (1832-1837), Winchendon, MA (1837-1842), and Bristol, NH (ca.
            1842-1850). He also organized the Temperance Society in Shoreham, VT in 1828. He was the
            father of Levi P. Morton, Vice-President under U.S. President Benjamin Harrison
            (1889-1893).</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_b88472ae92aafc12f4d84ca3e1de4327">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Seven complete and five fragments of handwritten sermons dealing with various Biblical
            texts and subjects.</p>
      </scopecontent>
